cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the joint design of transmit precoding and receiver design to maximize the utility vector including the achieved data rates and the harvested energies of all users simultaneously. This falls under the scope of information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses a time-switching co-located simultaneous wireless information and power transfer (SWIPT) system consisting of multiple multi-antenna access points which serve multiple single antenna users. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a multi-objective optimization framework to design jointly the Pareto optimal beamforming vector and the TS ratio for each receiver. This falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the trade-off between harvested energy and information data rate objectives and shows the effect of optimizing the precoding strategy and TS ratio on this trade-off. This falls under the scope of multimedia. 
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper deals with a system consisting of multiple multi-antenna access points which serve multiple single antenna users. This falls under the scope of multi-agent systems.
